Note that water '''should not be used''' as a solvent for lithium aluminium hydride, which would react as in the following equation.
: LiAlH<sub>4</sub> + 4 H<sub>2</sub>O → Li<sup>+</sup> + Al<sup>3+</sup> + 4 OH<sup>-</sup> + 4 H<sub>2</sub>

==Crystal structure==
[[Image:Lialh4struct.jpg|thumb|The crystal structure of LAH. Li atoms are blue and AlH<sub>4</sub> tetrahedra are red. The unit cell border is marked by a black line.]] 

The [[crystal structure]] of LAH belongs to the [[monoclinic]] crystal system and the [[space group]] is P2<sub>1</sub>c. The crystal structure of LAH is illustrated to the right. The structure consists of [[Li]] [[atom]]s surrounded by five AlH<sub>4</sub> [[tetrahedron|tetrahedra]]. The Li atoms are bonded to one [[hydrogen]] atom from each of the surrounding tetrahedra creating a [[bipyramid]] arrangement. The side lengths of the [[unit cell]] are approx. a=4.82, b=7.81 and c=7.92, and the β angle is approx. 112 °. At high pressures (&gt;2.2GPa) a phase transition into β-LAH occurs.

